  <p>
    This technical report details the architectural blueprint, data pipeline integrations, stylesheet systems, and 
    critical engineering decisions made during the design and development of the Lendsqr Admin Dashboard. Built on top 
    of Next.js, TypeScript, Supabase, and SCSS, this solution represents a production-ready system constructed 
    according to strict visual guidelines and robust state management principles.
  </p>

  <div class="divider-line"></div>

  <!-- Section 1: Project Overview -->
  <h2>Project Overview</h2>
  <p>
    The Lendsqr Admin Dashboard application is a mission-critical operations portal designed for management of 
    borrowers, account parameters, credit facilities, and financial profiles. The primary objective is to 
    provide administrators with an intuitive, dense, and interactive system for managing hundreds of thousands of users. 
  </p>
  <p>
    The implementation covers:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>An enterprise-grade login screen featuring rigid validation, mock authorization routing, and pixel-perfect layouts.</li>
    <li>A multi-metric dashboard featuring unified system analytics counters (Total Users, Active Users, Users with Loans, Users with Savings).</li>
    <li>An advanced user directory table capable of paginating, filtering (across 6 dynamic criteria: Organization, Username, Email, Date, Phone Number, and Status), sorting, and performing context-aware administrative operations (Blacklist and Activate).</li>
    <li>A deep user inspection module that maps comprehensive core records (Personal Profile, Education and Employment, Socials, and Guarantor Details) into structured tabbed views.</li>
  </ul>

